@xoie_f I think I understand what you mean, but I’m not sure it’s illuminating to think of “the government” as doing any one thing or having a single perspective. Within Congress, the body that carries out impeachment, many Republicans were still supportive of Nixon. Only when enough of them flipped, after the tapes came out, did he resign. Today we have a similar case—only one R has come out saying we should begin impeachment proceedings. Without more support from the Republican (and center-right  Democrats), congress may not begin impeachment and will certainly not convict.
